cked the server."},"rbl_whitelist_greylist_common_mail_providers":{"label":"Exempt servers in the Greylisting “Common Mail Providers” list from RBL checks","help":"If enabled, the system will not run RBL checks on mail from an IP address block in the Greylisting “Common Mail Providers” list."},"acl_requirehelonold":{"help":"Require incoming SMTP connections to send a HELO that does not match this server&rsquo;s local domains.","label":"Require remote (domain) HELO"},"acl_spam_scan_secondarymx":{"help":"When enabled, mail that is sent to the primary mail exchanger for domains that are listed in /etc/secondarymx will be scanned with Apache SpamAssassin&trade;","label":"Enable Apache SpamAssassin&trade; for secondary MX domains"},"custom_mailhelo":{"label":"Reference /etc/mailhelo for custom outgoing SMTP HELO","help":"Send HELO based on the domain name in /etc/mailhelo (<a href=\"https://go.cpanel.net/eximdiffip\" target=\"_blank\">more information</a>)"},"trusted_mail_hosts_ips_button":{"help":"Hosts or IP addresses that should be exempt from all spam checks at SMTP time, except recipient verification. Hosts or IP addresses you enter here are stored in /etc/trustedmailhosts.","button":"Edit","label":"Only-verify-recipient"},"spamassassin_plugin_P0f":{"help":"Passive OS Fingerprinting must be enabled in the Service Manager for this plugin to be effective","label":"Enable Passive OS Fingerprinting for Apache SpamAssassin™"},"acl_ratelimit_spam_score_over_int":{"label":"Apache SpamAssassin&trade;: ratelimit spam score threshold","help":"Ratelimit hosts which transport messages with a spam score above this number. (positive or negative, single digit after a decimal point allowed)","undef":"No ratelimiting by spam score"},"acl_deny_rcpt_hard_limit":{"undef":"No disconnection based on number of recipients","help":"Disconnect and ratelimit any connection that specifies more than this number of recipients for a single message. NOTE: The RFCs specify that SMTP servers should 