y recipient addresses after this number have been specified for a single message. NOTE: The RFCs specify that SMTP servers should accept at least 100 RCPT commands for a single message.","undef":"No rejection based on number of recipients"},"manage_rbls_button":{"label":"Manage Custom RBLs","button":"Manage"},"tls_require_ciphers":{"label":"SSL/TLS Cipher Suite List"},"acl_spamcop_rbl":{"help":"Reject mail at SMTP time if the sender host is in the bl.spamcop.net RBL. [<a href=\"http://spamcop.net/bl.shtml\" target=\"_blank\">INFO</a>]","label":"RBL: bl.spamcop.net"},"filter_attachments":{"label":"Attachments: Filter messages with dangerous attachments"},"trusted_mail_users_button":{"button":"Edit","help":"Users on the system that may set the From: header to anything they like when \"Rewrite From: header to match actual sender\" is enabled.","label":"Trusted mail users"},"sender_verify_bypass_ips_button":{"help":"IP addresses for which to bypass SMTP-time sender verification checks","button":"Edit","label":"Sender verification bypass IP addresses"},"message_linelength_limit":{"label":"Maximum line length for SMTP transports","help":"This option sets the maximum line length in bytes, that the SMTP transports will send. Any messages with lines exceeding the given value will fail and a failure (\"bounce\") message will, if possible, be returned to the sender."},"spammer_list_ips_button":{"help":"IP addresses from which SMTP connections are dropped unconditionally","button":"Edit","label":"Blacklisted SMTP IP addresses"},"acl_0tracksenders":{"label":"Log sender rates in the exim mainlog.  This can be helpful for tracking problems and/or spammers."},"systemfilter":{"undef":"None (disable)","help":"The system filter file is usually stored as /etc/cpanel_exim_system_filter. [<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.exim.org/exim-html-current/doc/html/spec_html/ch43.html\">INFO</a>] Custom values must be existing files.","label":"System Filter File"},"malware_deferok":{"help":